<Service xmlns="http://www.gip.com/xyna/xdev/xfractmod" Version="1.8" TypeName="ExampleWorkflow" TypePath="xyna.example.workflows" Label="Example Workflow">
  <Meta>
    <Documentation>Workflows are processes that describe what happens to data, while services are the places to handle how data is manipulated.


- Wokflows can have inputs and outputs

- Inputs and outputs of workflows MUST be Xyna datatypes

- Inputs and outputs of workflow steps MUST be Xyna datatypses

- All inputs are immutable, you MUST use a servcie, a subworkflow or a mapping to create a new instance with altered or new data.</Documentation>
  </Meta>
